The paper deals with clustering, which is a common topic in machine learning and data mining. The use of a graph partitioning approach suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The focus on cluster quality measures and load-balanced clustering suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The use of a similarity function and pairwise similarities suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of a polynomial algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the focus on discovering natural groups in datasets suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
